headline: Tesla Is Struggling — The Global EV Market Isn't
summary: Tesla's (NASDAQ:TSLA) relentless sales slump has captured headlines in recent weeks, but that doesn't reflect the reality of the global EV market. Electric vehicle sales fell 4% in North America in 2025 due in large part to the expiration of the Federal EV tax credit. While Tesla and other automakers were hurt in the U.S., the global demand was much better.
